The paper deals with the problem of temporal grounding of sentences in videos, which involves understanding both visual and textual information. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a two-stage model that involves matching visual and textual features, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval techniques for identifying the best-matched proposal, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
